---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy" description="Dunstan Research Group editorial policy — independence, corrections, AI disclosure, and publication standards.">
  <div class="container" style="padding-top:4rem;padding-bottom:4rem;max-width:800px;">
    <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">How we maintain independence, handle corrections, and disclose the use of AI-assisted drafting.</p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Editorial Independence</h2>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
      Dunstan Research Group is editorially independent. Our researchers select topics, define criteria, and reach conclusions without approval from any vendor, investor, or sponsor. No external party may review a report prior to publication for the purpose of altering conclusions.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Conflict of Interest Policy</h2>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
      Researchers and reviewers disclose financial holdings, advisory roles, and prior employment relevant to coverage areas. We do not cover entities in which a team member holds a material position. Reviewers with a current commercial relationship to a covered subject are recused.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Correction Policy</h2>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
      We publish corrections when supported by qualifying evidence. Our target service levels are:
    </p>
    <ul style="margin-top:1rem;padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:1.9;">
      <li><strong>Acknowledge</strong> within 5 business days of a valid submission.</li>
      <li><strong>Decide</strong> within 15 business days whether to issue a correction, update, or rebuttal.</li>
      <li><strong>Publish</strong> corrections at the top of the affected report with a dated note.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">AI Disclosure Policy</h2>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
      We may use AI-assisted tools for drafting, summarization, and editing. All AI-generated content is reviewed by human researchers for accuracy, sourcing, and tone. We do not publish AI-generated claims without human verification against documented evidence.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Prohibited Content</h2>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
      We do not publish fabricated statistics, invented awards, anonymous accusations, or conclusions that exceed the evidence presented. Endorsements and recommendations are framed as findings tied to stated criteria, not universal truths.
    </p>

    <h2 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Publication Standards</h2>
    <p style="margin-top:1rem;line-height:1.8;">
      Every published report includes a research question, criteria, evidence classes, findings, proof gaps, limitations, source notes, disclosure, and a correction pathway. Reports without sufficient evidence to meet our gating tests remain in draft or are not published.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
